    <!-- Cookies -->
    <Section bg="white" id="cookies">
      <SectionTitle color="green" textalign="left">Cookies Policy</SectionTitle>

      <div class="mt-[2rem]">
        <p>
          We use cookies to enhance your experience on https://d2l.sg. This
          Cookie Policy is part of D2L.sg’s Privacy Policy and provides
          information about the use of cookies between your device and our site.
          It also includes details about third-party services that may use
          cookies as part of their operations, though these third-party services
          are not covered by our policy.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-[1rem]">
          If you do not wish to accept cookies from us, you can instruct your
          browser to refuse cookies from https://d2l.sg. However, this may
          affect your ability to use certain features and services on our
          website.
        </p>

        <ul class="mt-[1rem] flex flex-col gap-y-[1rem]">
          <li>
            <h4 class="text-orange font-bold">About a Cookie</h4>
            <p class="mt-[1rem]">
              A cookie is a small piece of data that a website stores on your
              device when you visit. It typically contains information about the
              website itself, a unique identifier that enables the site to
              recognize your browser upon returning, additional data serving the
              purpose of the cookie, and the cookie’s lifespan.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-[1rem]">
              Cookies are used to enable certain functionalities (e.g., logging
              in), track site usage (e.g., analytics), store user settings
              (e.g., timezone, notification preferences), and personalize
              content (e.g., advertising, language preferences).
            </p>
            <p class="mt-[1rem]">
              Cookies set by the website you are visiting are called
              "first-party cookies" and usually only track your activity on that
              specific site. Cookies set by other sites or companies (i.e.,
              third parties) are termed "third-party cookies" and can track you
              across multiple sites using the same third-party service.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h4 class="text-orange font-bold">
              Types of Cookies and How We Use Them
            </h4>
            <ol class="mt-[1rem] list-decimal">
              <li class="mt-[1rem]">
                1. Essential Cookies

                <p>
                  Essential cookies are crucial for the operation of our
                  website, enabling core functionalities such as user logins,
                  account management, shopping carts, and payment processing. We
                  use essential cookies to enable these functionalities on our
                  website.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li class="mt-[1rem]">
                2. Performance Cookies

                <p>
                  Performance cookies track how you use our website during your
                  visit, without collecting personally identifiable information.
                  This information is typically anonymous and aggregated,
                  helping us understand visitor usage patterns, diagnose issues,
                  and make strategic decisions to enhance overall website
                  experience. These cookies may be set by our website
                  (first-party) or by third-party services. We use performance
                  cookies to improve our site.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li class="mt-[1rem]">
                3. Functionality Cookies

                <p>
                  Functionality cookies collect information about your device
                  and any settings you configure on our website (e.g., language
                  and timezone settings). This information allows us to provide
                  customized, enhanced, or optimized content and services. These
                  cookies may be set by our website (first-party) or by
                  third-party services. We use functionality cookies for
                  selected features on our site.
                </p>
              </li>
              <li class="mt-[1rem]">
                4. Targeting/Advertising Cookies

                <p>
                  Targeting/advertising cookies are used to determine what
                  promotional content is more relevant to you and your
                  interests. They help us deliver targeted advertising and limit
                  the number of times you see an ad, enhancing the effectiveness
                  of our marketing campaigns and the quality of the content you
                  see. These cookies may be set by our website (first-party) or
                  by third-party services. Targeting/advertising cookies set by
                  third parties may track you on other websites that use the
                  same third-party service. We use targeting/advertising cookies
                  to deliver relevant promotional content.
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h4 class="text-orange font-bold">
              Third-Party Cookies on Our Site
            </h4>
            <p class="mt-[1rem]">
              We may engage third-party companies and individuals on our website
              for various services, such as analytics providers and content
              partners. These third parties may set cookies on your device to
              deliver their services. As we have no control over third-party
              cookies, they are not covered by D2L.sg’s Cookie Policy.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h4 class="text-orange font-bold">
              Our Third-Party Privacy Promise
            </h4>
            <p class="mt-[1rem]">
              We review the privacy policies of all our third-party providers to
              ensure their practices align with ours. We will never knowingly
              include third-party services that compromise or violate the
              privacy of our users.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li>
            <h4 class="text-orange font-bold">
              How You Can Control or Opt-Out of Cookies
            </h4>
            <p class="mt-[1rem]">
              If you do not wish to accept cookies from us, you can instruct
              your browser to refuse cookies from our website. Most browsers are
              set to accept cookies by default, but you can update these
              settings to refuse cookies altogether or to notify you when a
              website is trying to set or update a cookie.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-[1rem]">
              If you access our website from multiple devices, you may need to
              update your settings on each device individually.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-[1rem]">
              Please note that blocking all cookies may impact your experience
              and limit access to certain features and content on our site.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </Section>
  </Section>
</Layout>
